  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For example, Xia et al. (2024) propose a human-machine collaborative multimodal learning method for recognizing cross-subject olfactory preferences, combining olfactory EEG and electronic nose data.",
    "The approach successfully extracts both common and individual features, achieving superior recognition performance compared to state-of-the-art methods.",
    "In addition, Wang et al. (2024) propose an integrated multimodal sensing strategy for scent digitalization, combining various sensing techniques to capture the full complexity of scents.",
    "This approach aims to enhance scent composition analysis and inspire advancements in scent-sensing systems, addressing the limitations of current single-sensing methods.",
    "The applications of AI in olfactory recognition are extensive and transformative, impacting various sectors such as food science, environmental monitoring, and healthcare."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, Xia et al. (2024) propose a human-machine collaborative multimodal learning method for recognizing cross-subject olfactory preferences, combining olfactory EEG and electronic nose data.",
    "In addition, Wang et al. (2024) propose an integrated multimodal sensing strategy for scent digitalization, combining various sensing techniques to capture the full complexity of scents."
